The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, June 30 (PTI): The Armed Forces Tribunal today directed the government to give benefits of war disability pension without any distinction between pre and post-2006 retirees.           
	According to the existing policy, the personnel who have retired after 2006 get more benefits under the pension than those who have left service before that year.                   
	London (PTI): Indians travelling to Britain, please note: the 20 note featuring composer Edward Elgar will be withdrawn from circulation from Thursday and will be replaced with a note of the same denomination but featuring 18th century economist Adam Smith. Most banks, building societies and post offices will, however, accept the Elgar 20 notes for deposit and other transactions, for some time.                  
	Mhow, MP (PTI):Veteran constitutional expert and noted advocate B.M. Masani passed away at the Parsi General hospital in Mumbai on Wednesday. He was 86. Masani was suffering from lung ailments for the past six weeks and had gone to Mumbai for treatment, said a family member.                   
	 New Delhi(PTI): The pension of retired IPS officer S.P. S. Rathore, who had been convicted of molesting teenager Ruchika Girhotra, has been stopped. It has been withheld in full on permanent basis, the Union home ministry said.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): A sub-inspector shot himself dead using his service revolver in the Kanjhawla police station. The reason is not known.
                                                                                                                                              
